מישׁר / mêyshâr / may-shawr'

=== Etymology ===

From {{HH|3474}}; 
=== Noun ===
evenness, that is, (figuratively) prosperity or concord; also straightness, that is, (figuratively) rectitude (only in plural with singular sense; often adverbially): - agreement, aright, that are equal, equity, (things that are) right (-eously, things), sweetly, upright (-ly, -ness).